Wow, thanks so much for this. Got me out of a real bind. Unfortunately, the link @Arad gives to the uploadify forum for the original solution no longer exists, so here's what I did to get the above to work:

Around my '<input type="file">' I did:

    <div class="uploadifyFixer">
        <input type="file" name="photo1" />
    </div>

Then, when initializing sortable in my '$(document).ready' I did:

    $('#sortable').sortable({
        cancel: '.uploadifyFixer',
        // etc.
    });

(Sorry for the lack of formatting, comments unfortunately aren't as flexible as answers!)

I got what I was missing. Actually in may cases the data was overlapping which needs the comment to overlap too. And the error was when there is already comment inserted in a particular cell, it wasn't allowing me to insert one more like replacing it with new one. So the Solution is to clear previous Cell coment and add new one to it.Microsoft.Office.Interop.Excel.Range range = objCopy.Cells[j + Convert.ToInt16(StartRow["StartRow"]), 4];
                                            range.ClearComments();
                                            range.AddComment("From Cogency");

